grihalakshmi ( english : educated wife ) ( hindi : गृहलक्ष्मी , lit . house-goddess of wealth ) is a 1934 hindi social family melodrama film directed by sarvottam badami with story by dr. jayant shyam and cinematography by faredoon irani .   the film was produced by sagar movietone and had music by s. p. rane .   the cast included sabita devi , jal merchant , yakub , kamala devi , k. c. dey , swaroop rani and asooji .   badami became well known for directing " sensitive " and " socially relevant " films like grihlakshmi for sagar movietone .   the film was a remake of the earlier bhaneli bhamini ( 1927 ) which had a relevant social message to impart against sexually transmitted disease according to an advertisement in the bombay chronicle in 1927 .   this 1934 version differed in context showing an educated steadfast wife going through humiliation at the hands of her husband , but continuing to stay with him .